Key Account Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia - PT Monroe Consulting Group
Key Account Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Key Account Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading consumer goods and personal care companies. Our respected client is seeking a sales professional, preferably with experience working in a multinational consumer goods or pharmaceutical company, for the job of Key Account Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will report directly to the National Key Account Manager. Key job responsibilities will include: Develop and implement the sales strategy per customer in alignment with the Company’s strategic objectives and to manage the customer relationship on an ongoing basisResponsible for a key customersThe job has accountability for the full scope of company’s commercial interaction with the customer, ranging from the development of sales strategy per customer to the management of promotional activitiesThe role requires close cross functional interaction with trade marketing, planning, marketing, logistics, finance, and ISDelivery of   agreed account P&L  as per company objectivesAgree on strategic priority for a customer with the NKAM and develop a full year account master plan in line with sales master plan. The plan should be on the basis of category trend in the account/company brand trend/Nielsen inputs/internal 4P data/Panel data as shared by the Trade Marketing teamPlanning  for 4P LSM implementation at the customer level on the basis of insights and learnings drawn from the GSMsConvert the plans into convincing selling story for the accountDeveloping annual trading terms to optimizing the cost of business in account and deliver the financial and 4P objectivesMonitoring the performance of initiatives in account master plan against the KPIs, course correcting for deviationsTrade investment to be in line with the plan and to deliver the agreed ROIEvaluate  the activities and incorporate learnings for bettering the programs in futureCommunicate the plans to the field team and take a feedback from the field team on executionRetain key customers through the development of strong relationships by conducting regular meetings to discuss account performance and to address client concerns and ensure the resolution of issues in a timely mannerNegotiate and close Trading Terms with each and every account on an annual basisTimely and accurate claim submission from the accountsManaging and developing company’s position as a key partner/supplier to major customersEffectively managing/driving company’s presence in highly competitive categories Job RequirementsBachelor’s degree in sales, marketing or business administration with a Master’s degree in business administration preferredAt least 5-7 years of mandatory sales experience and key accounts or trade marketing experience in FMCG or pharmaceutical companiesProven track record in sales management with major retailersExperience influencing and engaging senior management in own and customer organizationsResults oriented, entrepreneurial and self-motivatedTenacious and resilient, driven to achieve even when faced with obstaclesLeadership and interpersonal skills capable of building strong working relationships and influencing and customers and internal teamsStrong commercial understanding of business issues and opportunitiesStrong understanding of sales and marketing strategy and planning issuesStrong analytical skills with ability to develop strategies, tactics and measurable implementation Fluent English All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to consumer@monroeconsulting.com
